Synthesis of silver nanoparticles
The primary goal of the paper was to investigate physicochemical properties and the bioactivity of the nanoparticles obtained in the presence of different natural extracts. Thus, during preparation of the extracts we followed the main steps of the synthesis conditions given in the literature (Castillo-López and Pal, 2014, Al-Kalifawi et al., 2015, Khalilzadeh and Borzoo, 2016, Ali et al., 2015, Siemieniec and Kruk, 2013, Kaviya et al., 2011, Ali et al., 2016).
For Ag nanoparticles synthesis AgNO3 and acetone were purchased from Avantor (Performance Materials, Gliwice, Poland). All fruits and vegetables were purchased from the local grocery store.
For all solutions, the pH value was measured, and the obtained values are presented in Table 1.
